<%- include('../partials/header') %>

<main class="min-h-screen bg-slate-50 text-slate-900">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-10 space-y-6">
    <header class="space-y-1">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">
        Last updated:
        <span class="font-medium"><%= new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-IN') %></span>
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-sm space-y-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-700">
      <p>
        Welcome to <strong>SpeakState.com</strong> (“we”, “our”, “us”). We operate a public information platform that
        provides MLA profiles, political topics, corruption/work data, election info, and user-generated reviews.
      </p>

      <p>Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use SpeakState.com.</p>

      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-4">1. Information We Collect</h2>
      <p><strong>1.1 Personal Information (provided by you)</strong></p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
        <li>Name</li>
        <li>Email address</li>
        <li>Reviews and posts you write</li>
        <li>Any profile details you submit</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="mt-3"><strong>1.2 Automatically Collected Information</strong></p>
      <p>We automatically collect:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
        <li>IP address</li>
        <li>Browser type &amp; device information</li>
        <li>Pages visited and time spent on the website</li>
        <li>Cookies for analytics and advertising</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="mt-3"><strong>1.3 Cookies &amp; Tracking</strong></p>
      <p>
        SpeakState.com uses cookies and similar technologies to improve your experience, analyze traffic, and show relevant advertisements.
        You can control cookies through your browser settings.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-4">2. Google AdSense &amp; Third-Party Ads</h2>
      <p>
        We use <strong>Google AdSense</strong> to display ads on SpeakState.com. Google may use cookies, including the
        <strong>DART cookie</strong>, to serve ads based on your visits to this and other websites.
      </p>
      <p>
        Users may opt out of personalized advertising by visiting Google’s Ads Settings:
        <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          https://www.google.com/settings/ads
        </a>
      </p>
      <p>
        Third-party vendors and ad networks may also use cookies to show ads on our site. We do not control these cookies and
        their use is subject to the respective third-party privacy policies.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-4">3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
        <li>Operate and improve SpeakState.com</li>
        <li>Display relevant political information and content</li>
        <li>Show personalized and non-personalized advertisements</li>
        <li>Monitor and prevent abuse, spam, and security issues</li>
        <li>Analyze usage patterns and website performance</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-4">4. User-Generated Content</h2>
      <p>
        When you post reviews, comments, or other content on SpeakState.com, you understand that this information may be publicly visible.
        You agree not to post sensitive personal data, illegal content, hate speech, or defamation.
      </p>
      <p>
        We may moderate, edit, or remove user content that violates laws, our policies, or basic community standards.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-4">5. Data Protection &amp; Security</h2>
      <p>
        We use reasonable technical and organizational measures (such as HTTPS and secure hosting) to protect your information.
        However, no method of transmission over the internet is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-4">6. Your Rights</h2>
      <p>You may request:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
        <li>Access to the personal data we hold about you</li>
        <li>Correction of inaccurate or incomplete data</li>
        <li>Deletion of your personal information, where applicable</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To exercise these rights, contact us at:
        <a href="mailto:contact@speakstate.com" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">contact@speakstate.com</a>.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-4">7. Third-Party Links</h2>
      <p>
        SpeakState.com may contain links to external websites (e.g., government portals, news articles, or reports).
        We are not responsible for the privacy practices or content of those websites.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-4">8. Children’s Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        SpeakState.com is not directed to children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.
        If you believe a child has provided us with personal data, please contact us and we will take appropriate steps.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-4">9. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The updated version will always be posted on this page with a revised “Last updated” date.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-4">10. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>
        If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
      </p>
      <p>
        📧 <a href="mailto:contact@speakstate.com" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">contact@speakstate.com</a>
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</main>

<%- include('../partials/footer') %>
